==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Orangeman
<hw>Or"ange*man</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>-men</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <def>One of a secret society,
organized in the north of Ireland in 1795, the professed objects of
which are the defense of the reigning sovereign of Great Britain, the
support of the Protestant religion, the maintenance of the laws of the
kingdom, etc.; -- so called in honor of <person>William, Prince of
Orange</person>, who became <person>William III.</person> of
England.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Orangeroot</ent>⟦br⟧
